description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The NHS Somerset Clinical Commisisoning Group (CCG) Quality and Nursing directorate have a development opportunity within the patient safety and risk team for a Band 6 Quality Improvement Facilitator for Patient Safety, on a full-time, fixed term basis, until 31 March 2021.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will support the Quality Lead for Urgent Care and Risk Management  and Quality Lead for Planned Care and Patient Safety, to manage the patient safety assurance process. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be required to work with clinical commissioners and CCG directorate managers to ensurerisk assessment, management and incident reporting are completed; as well as assisting in the promotion of quality improvement and patient safety within operational systems across the CCG and within all staff groups.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please ensure you have spoken to your current line manager about an internal secondment from your current post before applying.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information, please contact &lt;strong&gt;Karen Taylor, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Associate Director of Safety and Quality Improvement&lt;/strong&gt; via: 07780 676543.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post will close at midnight on Thursday 19th November 2020. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
